title: 10 most-asked Google questions about Cubs and Cardinals
text:
Face it, the Cubs-Cardinals NLDS has drawn a lot of attention, and with it some casual fans have decided to come along for the ride.
Some lack knowledge about either team, so where do they turn? Google.
According to the search engine, here are the five most-often asked “Why do …” questions by Cubs and Cardinals fans.
Start Slideshow »
Besides always having a great farm system and the best top-down management in MLB, they adhere to "The Cardinal Way." Third baseman Matt Carpenter once described it: "That's just the way we like to play the game -- never give an inch, keep fighting to the last pitch, grinding out at-bats, grinding out games, just giving it your all while you're out there. That's why we've been successful, and I don't think we're going to change that." | AP
They wear No. 14 in honor of Ernie Banks who died in January.
